cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use LLMbench in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "LLMbench: A Comparative Close Reading Workbench for Large Language Models"
abstract: >
  LLMbench is a web-based research instrument for the comparative close reading
  of Large Language Model outputs, enabling researchers to subject AI-generated
  text to hermeneutic scrutiny. Part of the Vector Lab family of research
  instruments for critical vector theory.
authors:
  - family-names: Berry
    given-names: David M.
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2147-1366"
    affiliation: "University of Sussex"
repository-code: "https://github.com/vector-lab-tools/LLMbench"
url: "https://vector-lab-tools.github.io"
license: MIT
version: "2.15.3"
date-released: "2026-04-24"
keywords:
  - large language models
  - close reading
  - digital humanities
  - critical code studies
  - computational criticism
  - AI analysis
  - vector lab
